<section class="performance-insight">
    <div class="insight-box">

        <h3 class="insight-title">
            <span class="accent-bar"></span>
            Who Stands Out at International Level?
        </h3>

        <p class="insight-text">
            Directly comparing international careers requires context, as the environments these players
            operate in are fundamentally different. Kylian Mbappé and Vinícius Júnior represent established
            international superpowers in France and Brazil—teams that dominate possession, control matches,
            and consistently reach the latter stages of major tournaments. Erling Haaland, by contrast,
            leads a developing Norway side with limited resources and less exposure to major competitions.
        </p>


        <p class="insight-text">
            Kylian Mbappé has built one of the strongest international records of his generation with France.
            He has scored <span class="highlight">55 goals</span> in
            <span class="highlight">94 matches</span> and consistently delivered in major tournaments,
            including <span class="highlight">12 World Cup goals</span> across two editions, proving his
            ability to perform on the biggest stages within an elite team.
        </p>
        <p class="insight-text">
            Erling Haaland represents a contrasting case. Despite playing for a Norway side with limited
            tournament exposure, he has scored <span class="highlight">55 goals</span> in just
            <span class="highlight">48 matches</span>, averaging
            <span class="highlight">1.15 goals per game</span>.
            This level of efficiency is among the best in modern international football and highlights his
            ability to produce elite numbers without the support of a dominant national team.
        </p>

        <p class="insight-text">
            Vinícius Júnior plays a more role-based part for Brazil. His international goal tally
            (<span class="highlight">8 goals</span>) is lower, but his impact is reflected through ball
            progression, movement, and creating space for teammates within a
            possession-heavy system.
        </p>

        <p class="insight-text">
            Overall, Mbappé and Haaland currently lead in measurable international output, each standing out as the key
            performer for their national teams. Vinícius, while already a world-class player, has not yet matched their
            statistical impact at international level, though his age and role suggest strong potential for future
            growth.

        </p>


    </div>
</section>



<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    const buttons = document.querySelectorAll(".tab-btn");
    const contents = document.querySelectorAll(".stats-content");

    function showContent(id) {
      // hide all
      contents.forEach(c => c.classList.remove("active"));
      buttons.forEach(b => b.classList.remove("active"));

      // show selected
      const section = document.getElementById(id);
      const button = document.querySelector(`.tab-btn[value="${id}"]`);

      if (section && button) {
        section.classList.add("active");
        button.classList.add("active");
      } else {
        console.error("Could not find section or button for id:", id);
      }
    }

    // Default = All Time Stats
    showContent("allTime");

    // Button clicks
    buttons.forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener("click", function () {
        showContent(this.value);
      });
    });
  });




  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    const links = document.querySelectorAll("a.dynamic-link");
    const basePath = window.location.pathname.split("/").slice(0, 2).join("/");
    // This will keep only the first subfolder, e.g., "/int-Stats"

    links.forEach(link => {
      const originalHref = link.getAttribute("href");

      // If it's already absolute or an external link, skip
      if (originalHref.startsWith("http") || originalHref.startsWith("/")) return;

      // Update href to include base path (not full current path)
      link.setAttribute("href", `${basePath}/${originalHref}`);
    });
  });

</script>